  <title>Documentation Updates</title>
  <para>
  This chapter lists content changes for this document since the release of
  <phrase role="productname"><phrase os="osuse">openSUSE速</phrase><phrase os="sles">SUSE速 Linux Enterprise Server</phrase><phrase os="sled">SUSE速 Linux Enterprise Desktop</phrase><phrase os="slerte">SUSE速 Linux Enterprise Real Time Extension</phrase></phrase> 11 SP3.
 </para>
  <para>
  This manual was updated on the following dates:
 </para>
  <!--list of xrefs, latest date sorted upmost-->
  <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <xref linkend="sec.admin.docupdates.sle12_ga" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/>
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  <sect1 xml:id="sec.admin.docupdates.sle12_ga">
    <title>October 2014 (Initial Release of <phrase role="productname"><phrase os="osuse">openSUSE</phrase><phrase os="sles">SUSE Linux Enterprise Server</phrase><phrase os="sled">SUSE Linux Enterprise Desktop</phrase><phrase os="slerte">SUSE Linux Enterprise Real Time Extension</phrase></phrase> 12)</title>
    <para/>
    <variablelist>
      <!--list of general issues that apply to all books-->
      <xi:include href="common_docupdates_general_i.xml" parse="xml"/>
      <varlistentry>
        <!--1. YaST Online Update-->
        <term>
          <xref linkend=" cha.onlineupdate.you"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        YaST provides an option to enable or disable the use of delta RPMs
        (Fate#314867).
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Before installing patches that require a reboot, you are notified by
        YaST and can choose how to proceed.
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry os="sles">
        <!-- 2. Gathering System Information for Support -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.adm.support"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Added the section <xref linkend="sec.admsupport.hostinfo"/>
        (Fate#315869).
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Added a section about the Supportconfig Analysis (SCA) tool and
        appliance: <xref linkend="sec.admsupport.sca"/> (Fate#315699).
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Added the section <xref linkend="sec.admsupport.kernel"/>
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=869159"/>).
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Updated and restructured the chapter.
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!-- 3. YaST in Text Mode -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.yast.text"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Added information on how to filter and select packages in the
        software installation module.
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!-- 4. System Recovery and Snapshot Management with Snapper-->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.snapper"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Updated the chapter and added new features (Fate#312751,
        Fate#316238, Fate#316233, Fate#316232, Fate#316222, Fate#316203,
        Fate#316222).
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Added the section <xref linkend="sec.snapper.snapshot-boot"/>
        (Fate#316231, Fate#316221, Fate#316541, Fate#316522).
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!-- 5. Remote Access with VNC -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.vnc"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        The default VNC viewer is now
        <systemitem class="resource">tigervnc</systemitem>.
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Added corrections on window manager start-up in persistent VNC
        sessions.
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!-- 6. Managing Software with Command Line Tools -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.sw_cl"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Removed documentation about Zypper's rug compatibility mode
        (Fate#317708)
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Rewrote <xref linkend="sec.zypper.query"/>.
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!-- 9. Booting a Linux System -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.boot"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Significantly shortened the chapter, because System V init has been
        replaced by systemd. systemd is now described in a separate chapter:
        <xref linkend="cha.systemd"/>.
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!-- 10. The systemd daemon -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.systemd"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Added a new chapter on systemd and the YaST Services Manager
        (Fate#316631, Fate#312568).
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        New section on loading kernel modules
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=892349"/>).
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <!-- 11. journalctl: Query the systemd Journal -->
      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.journalctl"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
      Added a new chapter
      (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=878352"/>).
     </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!--12. The Boot Loader GRUB 2 -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.grub2"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Replaced the GRUB Legacy documentation with a new chapter on GRUB 2.
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Support for LILO has been dropped.
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Added new section <xref linkend="sec.grub2.zseries"/>.
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!-- 13. UEFI (Unified Extensible Firmware Interface) -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.uefi"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Updated the chapter and added new features (Fate#314510,
        Fate#316365).
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Fixed
        <link xlink:href="http://doccomments.provo.novell.com/comments/25080"/>.
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!-- 15. Printer Operation -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.p"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
      Updated chapter and section according to new CUPS version and with PDF
      now being a common printing data format (Fate#314630).
     </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!-- 17. The X Window System -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.x11"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Updated the chapter to reflect dynamic configuration during each
        start-up.
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Updated <xref linkend="sec.x11.fontsys"/>.
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!-- 19. Basic Networking-->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.basicnet"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        NetworkManager ist now part of the Workstation Extension:
        <xref linkend="sec.basicnet.yast.netcard.global"/>
        (Fate#316888).
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Added section about new <command>wicked</command> framework for
        network configuration: <xref linkend="sec.basicnet.manconf"/>
        (Fate#316649).
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Mentioned additional options that can be added to
        <filename>/etc/resolv.conf</filename>:
        <xref linkend="sec.basicnet.manconf.files"/> (Fate#316048).
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry os="sles">
        <!-- 20. SLP -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.slp"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Re-wrote chapter to provide significantly more information on the
        <command>slptool</command> command.
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry os="sles">
        <!-- 22. The Domain Name System -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.dns"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        The YaST DNS module now supports configuring forwarders
        (Fate#309036).
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry os="sles">
        <!-- 23. DHCP-->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.dhcp"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Removed dhcpcd as it is no longer shipped (Fate#316111).
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!-- 25. Samba -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.samba"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Added section <xref linkend="samba.advanced"/>.
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Added section <xref linkend="samba.advanced.compress"/>.
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Added section <xref linkend="samba.advanced.snapshots"/>.
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!-- 26. Sharing File Systems with NFS -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.nfs"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Configuring NFSv4 shares is now mostly similar to NFSv3, especially
        the previously required bind mount setting is now deprecated
        (Fate#315589).
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem os="sles">
              <para>
        Mounting NFS volumes locally on the exporting server is not
        supported.
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem os="sled">
              <para>
        Removed section about NFS server configuration.
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!-- 27. On-Demand Mounting with Autofs -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.autofs"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Added a chapter on <systemitem>autofs</systemitem> (Fate#316185).
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry os="sles">
        <!-- 29. The Apache HTTP Server -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.apache2"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Removed references to mono and mod_mono as it was removed from the
        distribution.
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Updated the chapter to Apache version 2.4 (Fate#316067).
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Removed deprecated directive <literal>NameVirtualHost</literal> and
        updated <xref linkend="sec.apache2.configuration.manually.vhost"/>
        accordingly.
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Updated <literal>Order</literal>, <literal>Allow</literal>, and
        <literal>Deny</literal> directives with standard
        <literal>Require</literal>.
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Removed virtual "Snake Oil" company from
        <xref linkend="sec.apache2.ssl"/>.
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry os="sles">
        <!-- 30. Setting up an FTP Server with YaST -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.ftp"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para><systemitem class="resource">pure-ftpd</systemitem> was dropped
        (Fate #315176, Fate#316308).
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!-- 34. Power Management -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.pmanage"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Remove obsolete references to the <systemitem>pm-utils</systemitem>
        package.
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <!-- 36. Common Problems and Their Solutions -->
        <term>
          <xref linkend="cha.trouble"/>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Added new section <xref linkend="sec.trouble.boot.btrfs"/>
        (Fate#308679, Fate#315126).
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Removed section about deprecated YaST Repair module (Fate#308679).
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>Wi-Fi Configuration</term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Removed chapter about Wi-Fi configuration with YaST as Wi-Fi
        configuration can be done with NetworkManager: <xref linkend="cha.nm"/>.
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>Tablet PCs</term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Removed deprecated chapter about tablet PCs.
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>Bugfixes</term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Added the section <xref linkend="sec.admsupport.kernel"/>
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=869159"/>).
       </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
        Added a new chapter <xref linkend="cha.journalctl"/>
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=878352"/>)
       </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </sect1>
</appendix>
